page.title: 04Plants of the Fens
page.content: We went out to Farcet Fen.We took a flower book with us,and a map.We went down to the bridge by the old{River {Nene.}We found ragwort,elderflowers, fleabane,dandelions and buttercups.A lot of duckweed grew in the water. We went to an old track across the fen and these plants were growing; hemlock,red clover,white clover,common red poppy,speedwell,cow parsley, hogweed and stinging nettles.The hedge at the side of the track was of hawthorn and ash with some silver birch.Rosebay willow-herb grew in the bottom of the hedge.There are different grasses at the sides of the fields.Some of them are ryegrass,wild oats,cocksfoot and meadow barley.
